About the Department of Agriculture

The need for increasing agricultural production to supply food grains to the growing population began to be felt in the 19th century. As recommended by the Famine Commission of 1881, the Department of Agriculture was established in July 1883. The work began with the aim of providing necessary assistance from the government level to increase agricultural production in rural areas by including all departments related to the agricultural sector. Till 1907, the Departments of Agriculture and Land Records were functioning together. After the promising results of the experiment conducted by the then Director of Agriculture, Mr. Keating, in 1915-16 to stop soil erosion, soil conservation work was started from 1922.
